OneDrive storage limit update

We're updating the default storage limits for OneDrive for Business users in your organization.

What's changing:
- Default storage allocation increasing from 1TB to 2TB per user
- Additional storage available for users who need it
- Storage analytics dashboard improvements in OneDrive Admin Center

Benefits for your organization:
- Users have more space for files and collaboration
- Better visibility into storage usage patterns
- Simplified storage management workflows

This change will roll out automatically over the next few weeks. No configuration changes are required on your part.

Users will see the updated storage limits reflected in their OneDrive settings. They will receive a notification when their storage allocation is updated.

For more information about storage management, visit the OneDrive documentation center.
